tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"O you wrapped up in your clothes (i.e. the Prophet (peace be upon him))."
  73,2,"Offer prayer at night except for a little part of it."
  73,4,"Or increase it until you reach two thirds. Make the Qur’ān clear when you recite it and recite it slowly."
  73,6,"The hours of the night are more suited to the heart for recitation and more correct in speech."
  73,9,"The Lord of the East and the Lord of the West. There is none deserving of worship besides Him. So take Him as a Trustee Whom you rely on in all your affairs."
  73,14,"That punishment will occur to those who deny on the day when the earth and the mountains will shake and the mountains will become scattered flowing sand because of its extreme horror."
  73,18,"The sky will split because of its horror. Allah’s promise will be inevitably fulfilled."
  73,19,"This admonition - containing an exposition of the horror and severity of the day of judgment - is a reminder that is of benefit to the believers. So whoever wishes to take a path that leads to His Lord let him do so."